<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / Bentsen calls for rouble stability fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER NORMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Lloyd Bentsen, the US treasury secretary, yesterday revived the idea of a
Dollars 6bn (Pounds 3.8bn) fund to stabilise the Russian rouble, writes
Peter Norman in Madrid. Speaking at the IMF-World Bank annual meeting, he
made mobilisation of the fund dependent on Russia pegging the rouble on the
foreign exchange market in the context of a strong economic reform
programme. Observers speculated that his remarks were designed to inject
some confidence into the rouble. The west offered Russia a rouble fund last
year but Moscow has so far failed to meet the conditions for it to operate.
</TEXT>
