<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 94 / Bullfight star's costly gesture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Official proceedings have been started against one of Spain's most
successful and glamorous bullfighters - over a bull he did not kill. Jesuln
de Ubrique could be fined up to Pta10m (Pounds 50,000) and banned for six
months for refusing to deliver the death-blow during a corrida last month in
the southeastern town of Albacete. And that, in the strange world of
bullfighting, is definitely against the rules. Occasionally a bull that has
fought particularly bravely may be spared, at the discretion of the
president of the fight. But Jesulin de Ubrique broke all the codes by taking
the decision himself. It was his 122nd meeting of the season, breaking a
record set by the flamboyant Manuel Benitez, El Cordobes. By allowing his
first bull of the afternoon to leave the ring alive, he wanted to make a
gesture to his famous predecessor. The bull in question, ironically, was
called Executioner. The president of the event, a police official as often
happens, took the matter seriously and reported it. The case is now in the
hands of the civil governor's office.
</TEXT>
<XX>
