acquisition of part of the Savings Bank of Finland to achieve a 14 per cent
reduction in overall pre-tax losses, to FM870m from FM1.01bn.
A large part of Unitas's credit losses in the first eight months was caused
by the collapse of two groups - Haka, a construction concern, and Eka, a
retail and wholesale company.
