Michael Walsh, 44, who has helped build Ogilvy &amp; Mather UK into Britain's
second biggest advertising agency, has been made chief executive of O&amp;M's
European operations.
Harry Reid, 49, who has been the London-based chairman of the group's
European operations since 1990, is taking up a new role as chief operating
officer of O&amp;M Worldwide, a subsidiary of WPP. He will continue to be based
in London.
Walsh, who has been with O&amp;M for 11 years, will work with Reimer Thedens,
45, vice chairman of Europe since 1992, to jointly run all Ogilvy's European
operations, encompassing the region's fourth largest agency network and its
largest direct marketing network. Thedens, heavily involved in building up
the latter part of Ogilvy's business, adds responsibility for all key
financial and personnel issues in his new role.
