<TEXT>
Azerbaijan's President Haydar Aliyev imposed a state of emergency yesterday
after interior ministry troops held the general prosecutor captive overnight
to demand the release of jailed colleagues. The president said the seizure
of Mr Ali Umarov by the special interior ministry police amounted to a 'coup
d'etat'. He said that 'aggressive forces inside and outside the country are
